---
import { Image } from '@astrojs/image/components';
import { YouTube } from 'iconoir-react';
import neilHeadshot from '../../assets/images/neil_hughes_headshot_al.jpg';
import { YouTube as YouTubeEmbed } from '@astro-community/astro-embed-youtube';
import wocCover from '../../assets/images/wocCover.jpg';
---

<div class='space-y-6'>
	<div class='font-serif text-3xl'>
		Neil Hughes experienced <span class='text-4xl font-bold text-red-700'
			>anxiety</span
		> for most of his life...
	</div>
	<div class='text-right'>
		... well. Not <em>constantly</em>. Occasionally I was asleep, or
		watching the Vicar of Dibley.
	</div>
	<hr />

	<Image
		src={neilHeadshot}
		alt='Neil Hughes'
		class='rounded float-left pr-4'
		width={200}
	/>
	<div
		class='first-letter:float-left first-letter:inline-block first-letter:pr-2 first-letter:text-7xl'
	>
		Worrying was always what I did best. But eventually my worry habit
		spiralled out of control. After years of background anxiety that would <span
			class='text-lg font-bold'>spike</span
		> and <span class='text-sm text-zinc-700'>fade</span>, <span
			class='text-lg font-bold'>spike</span
		> and <span class='text-md text-zinc-800'>fade</span>, <span
			class='text-lg font-bold'>spike</span
		> and <span class='text-sm text-zinc-700'>fade</span>, one day my
		anxiety <span class='text-xl font-bold text-red-700'>peaked</span> and never
		went away.
	</div>
	<div>
		I spent months in constant fear. Each night I lay awake, afraid of how I
		would feel the next day. There seemed to be no escape from this cycle.
		It seemed that the only way out might be something drastic.
	</div>
	<div>
		Naturally, I didn't actually <em>tell anyone</em> how I felt. That would
		be silly.
	</div>
	<div>
		Finally, I couldn't tolerate it any longer. My coping strategy of "hope
		it all went away" was clearly not working anymore. I decided to figure
		out what was happening... and maybe even do something about it.
	</div>
	<div class='p-3'>
		<div class='pt-3 text-xl font-bold text-green-600'>
			<YouTube className='inline text-red-700 text-4xl' /> I tell the rest
			of my story best through this video:
		</div>
		<YouTubeEmbed id={'bM06o26PCDQ'} />
	</div>
	<a href='/books/walking-on-custard'>
		<Image
			src={wocCover}
			alt='Walking on Custard - Book Cover'
			class='rounded float-left pr-4'
			width={200}
		/></a
	>
	<div>
		I started writing down everything I learned about managing my anxiety,
		and somehow it turned into <strong
			>Walking on Custard & the Meaning of Life</strong
		>â€”a funny guide to life for anxious humans.
	</div>
	<div>
		It's an odd book, I'll freely admit, but it's the book I wished I could
		read when I was struggling the most. It mixes personal stories, helpful
		advice gleaned from experts, and little tales about wizards and aliens.
		(And lots of embarrassing stories about me, too.)
	</div>

	<div class='clear-left pt-3'>
		<span class='font-serif text-xl'
			>Now I don't fear my anxiety anymore.</span
		> I use my experiences to help others who may be going through the same thing.
		As well as the book, there's lots of articles on this website.
	</div><div>
		Plus I'm available to give funny & helpful talks about anxiety, online
		and in person. Let me know if that would be helpful to you!
	</div>
	<div class='text-right'>
		<a href='/speaking'>
			<button
				class='rounded bg-red-500 py-2 px-4 !text-white hover:bg-red-400'
			>
				need a funny speaker on mental health?</button
			>
		</a>
	</div>
</div>
